oader issues**\\n\\nI'm looking into line coverage in JVM and whether the native image might fail with an error related to `ClassLoader.loadClass`. It seems like the `RejectingClassLoader.loadClass` is throwing a `ClassNotFoundException`, which is making me think about using `Class.forName` for testing nested classes. I need to clarify how these class loading mechanisms work together and whether there are any specific pitfalls to consider here.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_pXQX1y4i3DKv8wAkJ9NBZDSs|fc_07fdd8ed298c7a6e0169f504303ba08194969852fc21a391e0", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/javax.mail/mail/1.4/src/test/java/javax_mail/mail/SocketFetcherTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage javax_mail.mail;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport com.sun.mail.util.SocketFetcher;\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.net.InetAddress;\nimport java.net.ServerSocket;\nimport java.net.Socket;\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport java.util.Properties;\nimport java.util.concurrent.FutureTask;\nimport java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit;\nimport java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicInteger;\nimport javax.net.SocketFactory;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class SocketFetcherTest {\n    private static final String PREFIX = \"mail.socketfetcher\";\n    private static final String SOCKET_FACTORY_CLASS_NAME = RecordingSocketFactory.class.getName();\n\n    @Test\n    void loadsConfiguredSocketFactoryWithClassForNameFallback() throws Exception {\n        RecordingSocketFactory.reset();\n        Properties properties = new Properties();\n        properties.setProperty(PREFIX + \".socketFactory.class\", SOCKET_FACTORY_CLASS_NAME);\n        properties.setProperty(PREFIX + \".socketFactory.fallback\",